http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/%E2%80%98ICOMAR-2016%E2%80%99-from-today/article14011172.ece

Shri Dharmasthala Manjunatheshwara Institute for Management Development (SDMIMD), Mysuru, is organising the International Conference in Operations Management and Research (ICOMAR 2016) on its premises here on January 21 and 22. The keynote speakers of the conference are Dr. Randy Carter, Professor Emeritus of Biostatistics, University of New York, Buffalo, U.S., and Dr. N. Muthukumar, President and Whole Time Director of Automotive Axles Limited, Mysuru and Chairman of CII Mysore and QCFI Mysuru sub-chapter. Several eminent speakers from the industry will address the sessions and among them is Mr Sadashiva Baligar, vice-president (manufacturing), Toyota Kirloskar Auto Parts Pvt. Ltd., Bengaluru. Those wishing to attend the conference can register as a participant, or as a presenter of a research paper or a case study, and interact with experts, fellow researchers, and academicians from the field, stated a press release. SDMIMD offers two years full time AICTE approved PGDM programme and is accredited by the National Board of Accreditation.For more details check http://sdmimd.ac.in/ICOMAR2016. All correspondence related to the conference should be mailed to icomar@sdmimd.ac.in, the press release added.